{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c2c3487b-491a-4312-bd0a-d9c30a0f1cc4","content":"I can help point you in the right direction, though dump **analysis** is outside the scope of the tools I have available (the `dump-collect` skill only covers *collecting* dumps).\n\nHere are the main options for analyzing your `.dmp` file:\n\n### `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the session:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `pe` (`printexception`) | Show last exception details |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap overview |\n| `dso` (`dumpstackobjects`) | Objects on the stack |\n\n### Other tools\n- **Visual Studio** – File → Open → pick the `.dmp` → \"Debug with Managed Only\"\n- **WinDbg** (Windows) – load SOS via `.loadby sos coreclr`, then use the same commands above\n- **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS) – `lldb --core your-file.dmp`\n\n### Quick start to find the crash cause\n```\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n# then inside the session:\n> pe           # print the exception\n> clrstack     # see where it crashed\n```\n\nWould you like help installing `dotnet-dump` or setting up one of these tools?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1059c4d6-4447-43f4-82ec-530ffad3e355","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for configuring and collecting crash dumps, and explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":487,"requestId":"A0D0:6C08C:A7BC97:CAD20A:6A013824"},"id":"36827f08-ca13-4fca-aaed-8d944fcf0e7e","timestamp":"2026-05-11T02:00:16.838Z","parentId":"fb06d4d5-3976-4699-93fe-ab375d1af4f0"}
